The Federal Executive Council has approved contract for the procurement of 4 electricity transformers to help improve power supply in the country.  Briefing State House correspondents after todayâ€™s meeting, Minister of Power, Sale Mamman said the transformers, will replace the transformers that have been in use for the past 35 years.  Also briefing, Minister of the FCT, Mohammed Bello said six memos were presented to council for over N85 billion cost of infrastructure related projects in Abuja, including the revision of contracts for the rehabilitation and expansion of the Outer Southern expressway to include one in the federal capital city.  Similarly, the Ministry of Humanitarian Affairs and Social Development presented a memo for the procurement of fertiliser under the emergency agricultural intervention for states affected by conflict insurgency and also the 2018 flood disaster.